data.name: deepcopy
data.description:
Returns a deep copy of the given object. Non-table objects are
                copied as in a typical Lua assignment, whereas table objects
                are copied recursively. Functions are naively copied, so
                functions in the copied table point to the same functions as
                those in the input table. Userdata and threads are not copied
                and will throw an error.

data.name: tbl_add_reverse_lookup
data.description:
Add the reverse lookup values to an existing table. For
                example: tbl_add_reverse_lookup { A = 1 } == { [1] = 'A , A = 1 }`

data.name: tbl_contains
data.description: Checks if a list-like (vector) table contains `value` .

data.name: tbl_count
data.description:
Counts the number of non-nil values in table `t` .
>

data.name: tbl_deep_extend
data.description: Merges recursively two or more map-like tables.

data.name: tbl_extend
data.description: Merges two or more map-like tables.

data.name: tbl_filter
data.description: Filter a table using a predicate function

data.name: tbl_flatten
data.description:
Creates a copy of a list-like table such that any nested
                tables are "unrolled" and appended to the result.

data.name: tbl_isempty
data.description: Checks if a table is empty.

data.name: tbl_islist
data.description: Tests if a Lua table can be treated as an array.

data.name: tbl_keys
data.description:
Return a list of all keys used in a table. However, the order
                of the return table of keys is not guaranteed.

data.name: tbl_map
data.description: Apply a function to all values of a table.

data.name: tbl_values
data.description:
Return a list of all values used in a table. However, the
                order of the return table of values is not guaranteed.

data.name: trim
data.description:
Trim whitespace (Lua pattern "%s") from both sides of a
                string.

data.name: validate
data.description: Validates a parameter specification (types and values).
